Flyers Beat Sabres 5-4 to Tie NHL Quarterfinal Series at One Game Each

-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 
2011-04-17T00:02:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-17/flyers-beat-sabres-5-4-to-tie-nhl-quarterfinal-series-at-one-game-each.html
The  Philadelphia Flyers  defeated
the Buffalo Sabres 5-4 in their National Hockey League Eastern
Conference quarterfinals.  The Flyers’s victory tied the best-of-seven series at one
game each.  With the teams tied at 3-3 after the first period, Ville
Leino and  Danny Briere  had goals in the second period to seal
the Flyers’ win at Wells Fargo Center in Philadelphia.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nancy Kercheval at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net  